__## Methodology__

Research, design, implementation, and testing were all part of the project's methodical development process. 
We concentrated on setting up our environment and planning our project during the first phase. GitHub repositories and 
documentation were used to find inspiration and open-source libraries. The first project structure was then made, along 
with a development environment. UI development and feature planning were completed during the second stage. A user
interface that has both dark and light themes was created using research on Python and HTML, and with help from AI. The third
stage concentrated on design improvement. Visuals with animations were added to the interface. The best way to implement 
cross-platform notifications was also determined by researching types of notification bots online. We decided on a Telegram bot because it is accessible.
Finally, the developmen of the main system modules was completed. Scheduling algorithms were used to create a working calendar
system. For the to-do list and calendar task manager, a task management module with complete CRUD functions (create, read, update, delete) was made.
Additionally, the notification subsystem was finished and tested to make sure reminders work as intended. Continuous documentation and code review were 
also done to maintain code quality and meet the project timeline.
